“OUR bodies were printed as blank pages to be filled with the ink of our hearts.” Taken from one of the world’s most famous investment bankers, Michael Biondi seemed to be on the money with this quote. He highlights how tattoos are ink painted on our bodies which reflect our hearts. While some may prefer something small and symbolic, others prefer something big and extreme on their bodies. This became evident when www.brightside.me looked at some of the world’s craziest tattoos. According to the publication, these are some of the world’s craziest ink ever: 1. Star fever  Reaching for the stars and putting them on her face was the order of the day. These stars were made famous by singer Rihanna. 2. Chess face  Putting your game-face on has never been better depicted than this chess-faced tattoo. Do you think this was the right move to make in terms of creativity? 3. Say my name!  A guy wanted to tattoo his own name. He used Google Translator to interpret it into Russian and ended up tattooing ‘no translation’ on his back. 4. What’s on the menu  This Norwegian teen got a McDonald’s receipt tattooed on his arm. 5. How you feel  One should not be shy to share their feelings. 6. Oops  Some mistakes stay with us forever. 7. True art  Check out my new tattoo!